    {
      "kind": "parameters",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The spacing preferences instance of the adjacent view.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "next"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The axis that the two views align on.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "axis"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return-value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A floating point value that represents the smallest distance",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "in points between two views that satisfies the spacing preferences",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "of both this view and the adjacent views on their shared edge.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Call this method from your implementation of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/Layout",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " protocol",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "methods if you need to measure the default spacing between two",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "views in a custom layout. Call the method on the first view’s",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "preferences instance, and provide the second view’s preferences",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "instance as input.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For example, consider two views that appear in a custom horizontal",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "stack. The following distance call gets the preferred spacing between",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "these views, where ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "spacing1",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " contains the preferences of a first",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "view, and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "spacing2",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " contains the preferences of a second view:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "let distance = spacing1.distance(to: spacing2, axis: .horizontal)"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The method first determines, based on the axis and the ordering, that",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the views abut on the trailing edge of the first view and the leading",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "edge of the second. It then gets the spacing preferences for the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "corresponding edges of each view, and returns the greater of the two",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "values. This results in the smallest value that provides enough space",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to satisfy the preferences of both views.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "This method returns the default spacing between views, but a",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "layout can choose to ignore the value and use custom spacing instead.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
